# Agent API cost estimates

Whenever you add or change anything that calls the TikTok agent / Anthropic API, **re-check button cost estimates** before finishing.

## Required on every agent action button

1. Render `<AgentCostBadge>` beside the trigger button (see Daily Planner, Script Writer, TikTok Agent).
2. Pass inputs that affect token usage:
   - `generate_daily_plan` → `totalVideos={totalPosts}` (or actual video count)
   - `generate_script` → `durationSeconds={duration}`
   - `agent_chat` → `messageChars={input.trim().length}`
3. After the action completes, pass `actualCost={lastCost}` from the API response so the badge shows real usage.

## Keep estimates in sync with implementation

Update `electron/services/agentPricing.ts` → `estimateAgentActionCost()` when you change:

- Prompt/instruction length or JSON schema size
- Context blocks (library, products, pacing, packaging research)
- Expected output size (e.g. full scripts per video, SSML, captions)
- Memory-store context assumptions (`memoryContextInput`, `memoryCacheRead`)

If estimates drift, tune `taskInput` / `taskOutput` per action — estimates should land within ~2× of typical actual costs.

## New agent-powered actions

When adding a new user-facing agent action:

1. Add action to `AgentActionEstimateParams` in `agentPricing.ts`
2. Add case in `estimateAgentActionCost()` with realistic token math
3. Extend `AgentCostBadge` props + `hub.d.ts` `estimateAgentCost` types
4. Wire `hub:estimate-agent-cost` in `main.ts` if params change
5. Return `cost` from the service (`requestAgentTask` / `sendAgentMessage`) and surface `actualCost` in UI

## Pricing table maintenance

- Rates live in `MODEL_RATES`; `PRICING_AS_OF` must match the source date
- Default model is `claude-sonnet-4-6` — estimates use the same model as the agent when possible
- Re-verify against [Anthropic pricing](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/about-claude/pricing) when models or rates change

## Done checklist (before marking work complete)

- [ ] Every new/changed agent button has `AgentCostBadge` with correct dynamic props
- [ ] `estimateAgentActionCost` reflects new prompt/output size
- [ ] `actualCost` wired after successful calls
- [ ] Build passes (`npm.cmd run build`)

Background-only agent calls (e.g. one-time product research) do not need a badge unless the user triggers them from the UI.
